Definition: The pore size of the filter used to collect particulate material from a sample (typically a water sample). Only the material collected on the filter is used in the analysis.
The smaller dimension of the sampling area of a device with a rectangular aperture (e.g. a grab or a trawl); the type of device is specified elsewhere.
The size class of the biological entities used for the observation. Specimens with sizes outside this range would not be included in the dataset.
The name or description of the method used to extract the biological material from its surrounding matrix.
The name or description of the method used to collect the sample or make the in-situ measurement or observation.
The mesh size of the sieve used to sort biological material from a sample (typically a sediment sample). The material that remains in the sieve is discarded.
The 2-dimensional size of the opening of a sampling device (e.g. a grab or a trawl); the type of device is specified elsewhere
The mesh size of the sampling net used to obtain the sample. The type of net is specified elsewhere.
The pore size of the filter used to exclude particulate material from a sample (typically a water sample). Only the material and liquid passing through the filter are used in the analysis.
The mesh size of the sieve used to sort biological material from a sample (typically a sediment sample). Only the material that remains in the sieve is used in the analyses.
The name of the gear or instrument used to collect the sample or make the in-situ measurement or observation.
The name or description of the method used to preserve the sample after collection and prior to the analysis.
The name or description of the method used to divide the sample into subsamples.
The larger dimension of the sampling area of a device with a rectangular aperture (e.g. a grab); the type of device is specified elsewhere.
The name of the platform used to make the sampling, measurement or observation.
The efficiency of the sampling instrument in catching the targeted specimen.
The diameter of the sampling area of a device with a circular aperture (e.g. a corer or a net); the type of device is specified elsewhere.
